<div><div><h2>--</h2></div><div>in the wake of sexual harassment allegations made against its four senior executives  dentsu aegis network has asked kartik iyer  praveen das  bodhisatwa dasgupta and dinesh swamy to step down.in a press statement  the company said  “dentsu aegis network has always believed in providing a safe environment at our workplaces which is free from any kind of harassment. we have a zero tolerance policy towards any kind of harassment at our workplaces.”in can be noted that  iyer and das  co-founded happy creative services  which was acquired by dentsu aegis network in 2016. it was then renamed to happy mcgarrybowen.dasgupta was a senior creative director of the same agency  whereas swamy recently joined iprospect india as national creative director.</div></div>